Distribution. Currently, this species is only known with certainty from Mt. Kupe and Mt. Nlonako (
Fig. 4
). Specimens from the two localities differ slightly genetically, but form one clade compared to the remaining members of the genus (see below). Morphologically they are indistinguishable. The two populations are consequently regarded as conspecific herein. The type locality of the species is on Mt. Kupe.
